headline.main: Haile Selassie of Ethiopia Dies at 83; Deposed Emperor Ruled Ancient Land 50 Years in Medieval Style Haile Selassie, as Emperor, Led-His Ancient Nation Slowly Into the Modern World

snippet: Haile Selassie, the last emperor in the 3,000-year-old Ethiopian monarchy, who ruled for half a century before he was deposed by military coup last September, died yesterday in a small apartment in his former palace. He was 83 years old.
